    <text>
        <body>
      
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N.Y.</placeName> <date>Friday</date>&#44;</p>
			<p><date>Pericope Jethro &#40;December&#41;</date></p>
			<p>&#40;<date>1848</date>&#41;.</p>
			<p>Peace&#44; etc&#44; etc to the</p>
			<p><addressee>Rabbi Isaac Lehser</addressee> of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Although for two years I have refrained<lb/> from writing about the New sect which is<lb/> called Reformers&#44; but&#44; nevertheless&#44; at the<lb/> insistence of several people of great<lb/> piety&#44; I could not refuse&#44; and my<lb/> intention&#44; is now to reply to the heretical<lb/> works which are appearing in <placeName>Baltimore</placeName><lb/> every month and bear the name of<lb/> Sinai. I refer especially to the last<lb/> book which was published with regard to<lb/> uncovering the head at the time of the<lb/> grace after meals. That is why I ask<lb/> you dear Sir&#44; to write to me on <date>Sunday</date><lb/> next whether you want to publish in the<lb/> Occident whatever I write. If so I shall<lb/> send it to you next week. Thus will I<lb/> know if I have found grace in your<lb/> eyes. Your friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Menachem</persName>&#44; son of <persName>Leib</persName></p> 
          <p rend="indent(11)"><persName>Goldsmith</persName>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">My address is <persName>Emanuel Goldsmith</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>101 Chatham St.&#44; NY.</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
